		"name": "Traseallo Driver App API",
		"description": "# Traseallo Driver App — Complete API Collection\n\nFull mobile API for the Traseallo delivery driver application.\nAll endpoints under `/api/driver-app/*` — a dedicated, self-contained API for the mobile driver workflow.\n\n## Base URL\n`{{base_url}}` — defaults to `http://localhost:4001`\n\n## Authentication\n- **POST /api/driver-app/login** returns JWT `token`, `user`, `driver` objects\n- All other endpoints require `Authorization: Bearer {{token}}`\n- Token is auto-saved on successful login via the Tests script\n\n## Complete Driver Workflow\n```\nLogin → Dashboard → View Orders → Accept/Reject → Pickup (en-route → arrived → confirm/fail) → Start Delivery → Scan Verify → Stop (arrived → complete/fail/skip) → COD Collect → POD (photo + signature) → Deliver/Fail/Return → Location Updates → Notifications → Earnings → Go Online/Offline/Break → Support → Logout\n```\n\n## Sections (19 Folders, 63 Requests)\nA. Auth & Profile (7) | B. Dashboard (1) | C. Orders & Route (5) | D. Pickup Flow (5) | E. Delivery Stops (7) | F. Barcode Scanning (3) | G. Proof of Delivery (4) | H. COD Handling (3) | I. Order Outcomes (3) | J. Route Progress (1) | K. Live Location (2) | L. Notifications (4) | M. Delivery History (1) | N. Earnings & Wallet (2) | O. Settings (1) | P. Shift & Availability (4) | Q. Support & Help (4) | R. Health & Branding (2) | S. Convenience Queries (3)\n\n## Key Notes\n- Login accepts username, email, or phone\n- Login auto-sets driver status to `available`\n- Logout sets driver `offline` and deactivates push tokens\n- All file uploads use `multipart/form-data` with field name `file`\n- GPS location: call every 10-30 seconds, batch upload when offline",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
